New Records: Harry Kane scored twice on his 100th cap for England.
Lee Carsley is the first England manager to win his first two competitive games and keep a clean sheet in both since Steve McClaren in 2006.
Key Match Events: Harry Kane scored a brace to secure a 2-0 victory for England over Finland.
Trent Alexander-Arnold created multiple chances and provided a key assist.
Lukas Hradecky made several crucial saves for Finland but couldn't prevent the goals.
England dominated possession and attempted 801 passes, the most in a single match in the 2024-25 Nations League.
Pre-Game Insights: Lee Carsley emphasized the importance of precise passing and possession-based football.
Harry Kane expressed pride in reaching 100 caps and discussed his motivation to continue performing at a high level.
Post-Match Reflections: Harry Kane expressed pride in his performance and his desire to continue scoring goals for England.
Lee Carsley praised Harry Kane's motivation and Trent Alexander-Arnold's passing ability.
Craig Hope noted Trent Alexander-Arnold's impressive performance and Harry Kane's class finishing.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played in heavy rain, affecting the conditions.
A minute's applause was held in memory of former England manager Sven-Goran Eriksson.
